body.name: PWM Fan Hub, PC Chassis Fan Hub, Cooling Practical for Computer Case with PWM Cable (#2)
features: There is an adhesive on the back of the hub PCB board for easy pasting on a flat place, and there is a fixed screw hole.

The power supply can be directly supplied by the power supply to reduce the load pressure of the main board. The temperature control line PWM is connected separately from the main board, so that both power supply and temperature control are correct.

The PWM interface is connected to the motherboard CPU fan interface, and the red is the dedicated interface for CPU fan (with speed measurement function). The black interface is a PWM conventional fan interface (no speed measurement signal, but does not affect the PWM function).
Expand the four‑pin port of a single motherboard into multiple ports for uniform speed adjustment. (If your fan is a 3‑pin fan, you can also plug it in, but PWM control speed cannot be achieved.)
Solve the lack of motherboard interfaces and concentrate on processing fan wires.
